## bq CLI

### Setup

```bash
# Install via gcloud CLI
gcloud components install bq

# Or full gcloud install
# https://cloud.google.com/sdk/docs/install

# Authenticate
gcloud auth application-default login

# Set project
gcloud config set project my-project
```

**Source**: [bq Command-Line Tool](https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/bq-command-line-tool)

### Command Format

```
bq COMMAND [FLAGS] [ARGUMENTS]
```

**Resource format**: `PROJECT:DATASET.TABLE` (bq) vs `PROJECT.DATASET.TABLE` (GoogleSQL)

### Core Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `bq query 'SELECT ...'` | Run query |
| `bq ls` | List datasets |
| `bq ls dataset` | List tables |
| `bq show project:dataset.table` | Table metadata |
| `bq mk dataset` | Create dataset |
| `bq mk -t dataset.table schema` | Create table |
| `bq cp src dest` | Copy table |
| `bq load dataset.table file schema` | Load data |
| `bq extract table gs://bucket/file` | Export |

### Query Command

```bash
# GoogleSQL (default in newer bq)
bq query --use_legacy_sql=false \
  'SELECT COUNT(*) FROM `project.dataset.table`'

# Short form
bq query --nouse_legacy_sql 'SELECT 1'

# Destination table
bq query --destination_table=dataset.result_table 'SELECT ...'

# Limit bytes billed (fail fast on expensive queries)
bq query --maximum_bytes_billed=10000000 'SELECT ...'

# Dry run (no execution, shows bytes scanned)
bq query --dry_run 'SELECT ...'
```

### Configuration (.bigqueryrc)

```ini
--format=prettyjson
--location=US

[query]
--use_legacy_sql=false
--max_rows=100
--maximum_bytes_billed=10000000
```

### Help & Debugging

```bash
bq version
bq help
bq help query
bq --apilog=stdout query '...'   # Log API calls
bq --format=prettyjson show ...  # JSON output with error details
```

**Source**: [bq CLI Reference](https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/reference/bq-cli-reference)

