## Storage Best Practices

### Clustering

**When**: Queries filter on high-cardinality columns; tables > 64 MB.

**Benefits**: Reduces bytes scanned; adaptively sized storage blocks.

```sql
CREATE TABLE dataset.table
PARTITION BY date
CLUSTER BY user_id, event_type
AS SELECT ...
```

**Source**: [Clustered Tables](https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/clustered-tables)

### Partitioning

**When**: Time-series or range data; need partition-level delete/expiration.

**Types**: Time-unit (DAY, HOUR, etc.), integer-range, ingestion-time.

**Avoid** when: Partitions < ~10 GB (excessive metadata); DML modifies most partitions.

```bash
# Create partitioned table via bq
bq mk --time_partitioning_type=DAY \
  --time_partitioning_expiration=259200 \
  project:dataset.table
```

**Source**: [Partitioned Tables](https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/partitioned-tables)

### Table/Partition Expiration

Set expiration on datasets, tables, or partitions to control storage cost.

