## Function Optimization

### String Comparison

```sql
-- ❌ SLOWER: REGEXP_CONTAINS
WHERE REGEXP_CONTAINS(dim1, '.*test.*')

-- ✅ FASTER: LIKE (when regex not needed)
WHERE dim1 LIKE '%test%'
```

### Approximate Aggregations

```sql
-- ❌ SLOWER: COUNT(DISTINCT)
SELECT dim1, COUNT(DISTINCT dim2) FROM table GROUP BY 1

-- ✅ FASTER: APPROX_COUNT_DISTINCT
SELECT dim1, APPROX_COUNT_DISTINCT(dim2) FROM table GROUP BY 1
```

### Quantiles

```sql
-- ❌ NTILE can cause "Resources exceeded" (global ORDER BY)
NTILE(n) OVER (ORDER BY sales DESC)

-- ✅ APPROX_QUANTILES (distributed, no global sort)
APPROX_QUANTILES(sales, n)
```

### UDFs

- **SQL UDFs** — Prefer; optimizer can inline
- **JavaScript UDFs** — Avoid when possible; spawns subprocess
- **Persistent UDFs** — Prefer over temp UDFs in queries

**Source**: [Best Practices for Functions](https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/best-practices-performance-functions)

